- Text: 
7. Risk Assessment Methodologies
Risk assessment methodologies define the way your organisation completes risk assessments. The
methodologies adopted must:
•
•
•
Meet all regulatory requirements
Be practical and scalable for the risk environments involved
Be appropriate for the skill and experience of those completing the risk assessments
Organisations have the following options when it comes to risk assessment methodologies.
i.
Selecting an existing and appropriate assessment methodology
ii.
Adopting components from multiple methodologies to create a bespoke solution
iii.
Creating a bespoke methodology
It is critical to understand that selecting or creating a risk assessment methodology is only one part of the
solution. Organisations must also provide the necessary training, support and tools.
