In many cases, a blended approach provides the most effective outcome.

9A. Risk Matrix (5x5) and Scoring Guidance
A 5x5 risk matrix is a widely used tool to support qualitative risk assessment by
assigning numerical values to likelihood and severity.
Likelihood Scale
1 - Rare (Highly unlikely to occur) 2 – Unlikely (Could occur, but not expected) 3 –
Possible (Might occur at some time) 4 – Likely (Will probably occur in most
circumstances) 5 – Almost Certain (Expected to occur frequently)
Severity Scale
1-Insignificant (No injury or negligible impact) 2 – Minor (First aid treatment required) 3
Moderate (Medical treatment / lost time injury) 4 – Major (Serious injury or long-term
health effects) 5 – Catastrophic (Fatality or multiple serious injuries)
Risk Scoring Method
Risk Rating = Likelihood × Severity
This produces a score between 1 and 25.
Example Risk Matrix
