13. Common Challenges
• Over-reliance on generic assessments
• Lack of workforce involvement
• Inappropriate methodology selection
• Failure to apply hierarchy of control effectively
• Poor communication of findings

14. Continuous Improvement
Effective risk assessment requires ongoing review:
• Incident and near-miss learning
• Operational feedback
• Audit findings
• Changes in legislation or processes

